Tania is currently pursuing her PhD in Computational Statistical Physics under my guidance, and she has consistently impressed me with her strong analytical abilities and profound knowledge of programming languages, including Python, R, C, C++, and MATLAB. Her proficiency with advanced software tools such as Tableau, Microsoft Excel, and SQL further complements her technical expertise. Throughout her research, Tania has applied machine learning techniques to cluster graphs, predict nonlinear system behaviors, and analyze results using extreme value statistics. Her ability to translate complex theoretical concepts into practical applications is truly commendable.

